This is the opening line of a drinking song. The lyrics are in {no' Hol:n}, and thus not grammatical in modern standard Klingon:
▶ {'ej HumtaH 'ej DechtaH 'Iw:sen:nolink}
   {'ej Doq SoDtaH ghoSpa' SIqral bIQtIq:sen:nolink}
   {'e' pa' jaj law' mo' jaj puS:sen:nolink}
   {jaj qeylIS molor mIgh HoHchu'qu':sen:nolink}
  "And the blood was ankle deep
   And the River Skral ran crimson red
   On the day above all days
   When Kahless slew evil Molor dead!"

▶ {qeylIS betleH bochvo':sen:nolink}
   {'et Duj wovmoHwI'mey:sen:nolink}
   {tugh nab 'ogh qeylIS:sen:nolink}
  "The lights from the ship
   Reflect on his bat'leth,
   Soon Kahless will devise a plan."[2, p.102-103]
▶ {lubejtaHvIS Heghna' mInDu':sen:nolink}
   {betleHvo' veqlargh mInDu' mIghDaq:sen:nolink}
   {'et tamghay:sen:nolink}
  "When the eyes of death are upon him,
   Light reflects off the bat'leth
   Into Fek'lhr's evil eyes."[2, p.104-105]
